title: [Unearthed Antiquities, Human]
description: This portion of the enclosure is wide, though not particularly deep.  The back half of the space is covered in a rough sand and dirt mixture, and a variety of different sedimentary rocks are interspersed throughout it.  Here are there, however, exhibits are visible, each seamlessly integrated into the scenery.  A brass plaque is stationed directly in front of the exhibits.
location: between Wehnimer's Landing and Zul Logoth
